column10:
Après une longue expérience dans la finance est particulièrement dans le support de family offices, j'ai pendant plusieurs années mis ma carrière entre parenthèse pour des raisons personnelles. 

J'ai conscience d'un profile  atypique tout en pensant pouvoir apporter des compétences recherchées pour un single Family office  ;

- ma connaissance des enjeux ;

- ma maitrise de nombreux process liés à leur suivi quotidien (administratifs, banques, avocats, personnel) par mon expérience chez Lombard Odier ;
- mon habitude du contact avec tous les interlocuteurs impliqués dans une grande famille ;

- mon expérience dans les attentes et le contact  de ces familles ;

- mon sens des responsabilités, mon indépendance et ma capacité d'anticipation.

C'est une décision raisonnée que de vouloir rejoindre le service d'une famille car c'est dans une relation directe, impliquée et sur le long terme que j'envisage la reprise de ma carrière. 

Dans l'attente devons rencontrer,

Dears,
I live in Annecy next to Geneva in Switzerland and I started to work in Geneva in 2016 for the CEO of a multinational listed holding company. I studied in France at University Jean Moulin in Lyon and I graduated with a Master degree in private law.
My expertise is harnessed through various senior roles, as EA in various companies and PA residing in Family Offices as well as Private residence. For the past 17 years, I worked with Executives and Boards from various backgrounds and nationalities, with 
their corporate and private portfolios.
True right hand supporting global interests and delivering seamless personal and business support for international Executives and high-profile individuals, I am highly committed to confidentiality and service quality, identifying and addressing Principal’s needs while ensuring timely completion of duties within fast-paced platforms. Skillfully forge and cultivate productive relationships within global, multicultural environments.
Demonstrated loyalty and talent in executive gate-keeping, I provides strict diary management and implementation of best practice to surpass executive goals.
Extremely flexible, I am able to quickly assess and act within dynamic, even in highly stressful environments.
I have a worldly understanding of the needs of a busy Principal with a multi-faceted lifestyle, whom needs a focused dedicated and principled righthand person to ensure that both private and business life is successfully harmonized.
I have always kept perfect discretion and worked to ensure the confidentiality of the clients and maintain at all the time a professional image of the company or the Principal.

Principal Technical Skills:
• Diary scheduling of meetings, travel, professional or private appointments, ad-hoc tasks;
• Calls and emails monitoring (FR/ENG/SPA);
• Maintaining communication with the Board, Shareholders meetings organization, Minutes;
• Corporate and legal support (mediation, court hearings, Intellectual property, link with lawyers and Swiss authorities);
• Overseeing and managing refurbishments and maintenance Projects;
• Events organizating and coordinating ;
• Growing and coordinating a team of staff, including payroll, schedules and holidays;
• Supervising, sourcing and coordinating a team of contractors, including builders, interior designers, architects, and project managers;
 Managing household or corporate finances, including invoices, bank accounts, and employee or executives expenses;
• Establishing and maintaining systems that help the office runs smoothly;

Please find attached my resume and specific documents. I am particularly interested in working for you, and I would strongly appreciate bringing my skills to your Executive. 
If you have any questions, please contact me at +33672914583 or
aurelie.baudart@gmail.com. I am available for an interview at your convenience.
I look forward to hearing from you.

Sincerely,

Aurélie Baudart
